text: {{Infobox settlement | name = Tartu County | settlement_type = County of Estonia | image_skyline = Veised Aardla poldril 2013.jpg | image_flag = Tartumaa_lipp.svg | flag_size = 125px | image_shield = Tartumaa_vapp.svg | shield_size = 75px | image_map = Tartu County in Estonia.svg | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = | seat_type = Capital | seat = Tartu | leader_title = Governor | leader_name = | area_total_km2 = 2992.75 | population_total = 150167 | population_as_of = Jan 2017 |population_rank = | population_density_km2 = auto | registration_plate = T | iso_code = EE-78 | website = | footnotes = }} Tartu County is a county in Estonia. The capital city is also named Tartu. Tartu is between Lake Võrtsjärv and Lake Peipsi. The Emajõgi river is in the county. Nature preserves take up about 10% of the county's land. The biggest of them being Emajõe Suursoo and Alam-Pedja. == Municipalities == The county is divided into municipalities. As of 2017, there is 1 urban municipality and 7 rural municipalities in Tartu County.
